"{\"uid\": \"latimes.com-delos-story-2024-08-07-paris-olympics-victor-montalvo-breaking-gold-medal-b-boy\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Rooted in the founding of hip-hop  more than 50 years ago,breakingwill make Olympic history as it debuts this weekend, and all eyes  will be on Team USA leaderVictor Montalvoto bring home the gold.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 197, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 144, \"end\": 152, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9883415711369343, \"rank\": 0.005565143281577294, \"text\": \"Team USA\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"There are only a few breaking athletes who can compete for a long time.\", \"from\": 199, \"to\": 271, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"And it's because you always have to reinvent yourself,\\\" Montalvo  toldThe Timesin June.\", \"from\": 272, \"to\": 359, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Montalvo's interest and talent for the sport started  when he was 6.\", \"from\": 361, \"to\": 429, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"His father and uncle, Victor and Hector Bermudez, respectively, first discovered the style in the late 1980s while living in the Mexican city of Puebla.\", \"from\": 430, \"to\": 582, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 452, \"end\": 458, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/RCA_Records\", \"score\": 0.9981493654953018, \"rank\": 0.0017513581739836321, \"text\": \"Victor\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q18127\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/RCA_Records\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/RCA_Records\"}, {\"begin\": 463, \"end\": 469, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hector\", \"score\": 0.9999999997535269, \"rank\": 2.3194931173161295e-10, \"text\": \"Hector\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hector\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hector\"}, {\"begin\": 559, \"end\": 566, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mexican_Americans\", \"score\": 0.769785843565603, \"rank\": 0.2888417082964168, \"text\": \"Mexican\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mexican_Americans\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mexican_Americans\"}, {\"begin\": 575, \"end\": 581, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Puebla\", \"score\": 0.9999837026635018, \"rank\": 1.62976020892465e-05, \"text\": \"Puebla\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Puebla\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Puebla\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Known as the Bermudez Twins,  they helped popularize  the style throughout the area.\", \"from\": 584, \"to\": 668, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 606, \"end\": 611, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Minnesota_Twins\", \"score\": 0.9999998720491103, \"rank\": 1.2795101808114392e-07, \"text\": \"Twins\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q12973014\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Minnesota_Twins\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Minnesota_Twins\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The family's early entry into breakdancing inspired Victor, who would go on to pursue it as well.\", \"from\": 670, \"to\": 767, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He is the current world champion.\", \"from\": 768, \"to\": 801, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"What I enjoy the most is losing yourself in the music.\", \"from\": 803, \"to\": 858, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"You are basically an artist onstage.\", \"from\": 859, \"to\": 895, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"You are drawing things onstage,\\\" Montalvo said in the June interview with The Times.\", \"from\": 896, \"to\": 980, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 970, \"end\": 979, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Times\", \"score\": 0.9999995740646225, \"rank\": 4.259352955991831e-07, \"text\": \"The Times\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q11032\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Times\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Times\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"You are basically putting together a puzzle to make a big painting, that's what breaking is all about.\\\"\", \"from\": 981, \"to\": 1085, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The   30-year-old Olympian has worked on refining his style with signature head spins and body contortions while standing out among other B-boys.\", \"from\": 1087, \"to\": 1232, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1105, \"end\": 1113, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\", \"score\": 0.9999999565652624, \"rank\": 3.8998845442990275e-08, \"text\": \"Olympian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I do this for the love of it,\\\" Montalvo said.\", \"from\": 1234, \"to\": 1280, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I do not do it for the competition.\", \"from\": 1281, \"to\": 1317, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I do not do it for the money.\", \"from\": 1318, \"to\": 1347, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I want to leave my own mark.\\\"\", \"from\": 1348, \"to\": 1377, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Competition aside,  breaking's inclusion  in the Olympics recognizes the efforts and talents of  the  B-boys and B-girls throughout the dance's history.\", \"from\": 1379, \"to\": 1531, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In addition to the Florida-born Montalvo, Team USA  also includesSunny Choi, known as B-Girl Sunny, who is from Queens,  N.Y., and was introduced to the sport  as a freshman   at the University of Pennsylvania.\", \"from\": 1533, \"to\": 1743, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1575, \"end\": 1583, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9883415711369343, \"rank\": 0.005565143281577294, \"text\": \"Team USA\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 1604, \"end\": 1608, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ada_Choi\", \"score\": 0.9999999957185537, \"rank\": 4.2813746604782284e-09, \"text\": \"Choi\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ada_Choi\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ada_Choi\"}, {\"begin\": 1654, \"end\": 1658, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_City\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.2798777226911722e-18, \"text\": \"N.Y.\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_City\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_City\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"At 21,Logan \\\"Logistx\\\" Edrais the youngest member  and has been dancing since  age  7.\", \"from\": 1744, \"to\": 1829, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Lastly,Jeffrey Louis, a.k.a.\", \"from\": 1830, \"to\": 1858, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1837, \"end\": 1844, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pinus_jeffreyi\", \"score\": 0.9999979721617461, \"rank\": 1.8571918285871914e-06, \"text\": \"Jeffrey\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pinus_jeffreyi\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pinus_jeffreyi\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"B-Boy Jeffro, is recognized for his creation of Fitbreak, a fitness program that brings together breaking and exercises, as well as his accolades in the dancing style.\", \"from\": 1859, \"to\": 2026, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1859, \"end\": 1864, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Breakdancing\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.775269175563101e-39, \"text\": \"B-Boy\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Breakdancing\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Breakdancing\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The four  will  face  athletes from more than a dozen countries, including Japan, France and China.\", \"from\": 2028, \"to\": 2127, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2103, \"end\": 2108, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan\", \"score\": 0.6239328418440782, \"rank\": 0.5874677918109285, \"text\": \"Japan\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan\"}, {\"begin\": 2110, \"end\": 2116, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9338021380300826, \"rank\": 0.03738825500308414, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 2121, \"end\": 2126, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.9990693442625268, \"rank\": 0.0005595042894100808, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"During   competition, participants are expected to showcase their style and abilities while a DJ spins unexpected beats.\", \"from\": 2128, \"to\": 2248, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2222, \"end\": 2224, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Disc_jockey\", \"score\": 0.9999999997694431, \"rank\": 2.3064214386306334e-10, \"text\": \"DJ\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Disc_jockey\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Disc_jockey\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They will be scored  on execution, musicality, originality, technique and vocabulary.\", \"from\": 2249, \"to\": 2334, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Each generation has its footprint so it can expand, but at the core it will never change.\", \"from\": 2336, \"to\": 2426, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Hip-hop is an Afro diasporic voice that calls for respect and at this point after 2020, nothing can erase the rooted aspect of hip-hop in Blackness,\\\" Puerto Rican B-Girl pioneer Ana \\\"Rokafella\\\" Garcia  toldDe Loslast year.\", \"from\": 2427, \"to\": 2649, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2441, \"end\": 2445, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Afro\", \"score\": 0.9986661290837267, \"rank\": 0.001333748913562721, \"text\": \"Afro\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Afro\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Afro\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The Olympics will be another iteration of this dance form and stand alongside the other cultural branches on this tree.\\\"\", \"from\": 2650, \"to\": 2771, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The  tournament starts with the B-girls  qualifier at 7 a.m. Pacific on Friday  and the final at 11 a.m.  Pacific.\", \"from\": 2773, \"to\": 2887, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Similarly, the B-boys  will compete at the same times, only on Saturday.\", \"from\": 2888, \"to\": 2960, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Follow Us  Cerys Davies is a reporting fellow at the Los Angeles Times.\", \"from\": 2962, \"to\": 3033, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3015, \"end\": 3032, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles_Times\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.6747262719448918e-22, \"text\": \"Los Angeles Times\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q11032\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles_Times\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles_Times\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She first joined The Times as an intern in the De Los section.\", \"from\": 3034, \"to\": 3096, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3051, \"end\": 3060, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Times\", \"score\": 0.9999995740646225, \"rank\": 4.259352955991831e-07, \"text\": \"The Times\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q11032\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Times\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Times\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In the Latino-focused vertical, she covered the growth of Latin music, profiled local artists and explored L.A.'s role in m\\u00fasica Mexicana.\", \"from\": 3097, \"to\": 3235, \"entities